            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3ECan%20you%20race%20on%20foot%20against%20horsemen%3F%20Jeremiah%20asks%20a%20pointed%20question%20about%20our%20level%20of%20commitment.%20The%20obvious%20implication%20is%20that%20if%20we%20grow%20tired%20and%20give%20up%20when%20dealing%20with%20relatively%20inconsequential%20problems%2C%20we%20will%20never%20be%20able%20to%20handle%20major%20problems.%20If%20we%20have%20problems%20dealing%20with%20grocery%20money%2C%20how%20will%20we%20be%20able%20to%20manage%20Kingdom%20finances%3F%20If%20we%20cannot%20keep%20our%20own%20house%20in%20order%2C%20how%20will%20we%20rule%20nations%3F%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ESometimes%20we%20twenty-first-century%20Christians%20feel%20as%20though%20we%20have%20it%20rough.%20The%20early%20Church%2C%20however%2C%20had%20it%20much%20rougher.%20They%20were%20indeed%20running%20with%20the%20horsemen!%20Paul%20commended%20the%20Thessalonians'%20faith%20and%20perseverance%2C%20saying%2C%20%22You%20received%20the%20message%20with%20joy%20from%20the%20Holy%20Spirit%20in%20spite%20of%20the%20severe%20suffering%20it%20brought%20you%22%20(1%20Thessalonians%201%3A6).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThe%20presence%20of%20greater%20challenges%20in%20our%20lives%20doesn't%20mean%20that%20God%20has%20left%20us%2C%20but%20it%20does%20mean%20He%20trusts%20our%20ability%20to%20run%20with%20the%20horses.%20With%20the%20help%20of%20God%2C%20you%20can%20outrun%20any%20challenge%20in%20your%20life%2C%20as%20Elijah%20did%20when%20he%20outran%20Ahab's%20horses%20all%20the%20way%20to%20Jezreel%20(1%20Kings%2018%3A46).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EGet%20ready%20for%20a%20new%20level%20of%20commitment.%20The%20foot%20race%20is%20over-%20the%20horses%20are%20coming!%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
